# Regression Test Recipes

A failing test written before the fix is the proof of the defect; the same test passing after the fix is the proof of the regression lock. Every fix shipped by this agent must leave behind exactly one (or a tightly-scoped few) regression tests. Sections referenced from the main agent file as `§N`.

> **Naming convention:** Regression tests should be named so future contributors know they exist to prevent a specific bug. Use `TestRegression_<short_name>_does_not_<bad_thing>` (Go) or `it("does not <bad thing> when <condition>", ...)` (Vitest). Add a one-line comment with the date and a one-sentence description of the original symptom.

---

## §1 — CRASH-CLASS LOCK-INS (P0)

### Go: panic / nil-deref regression

```go
// File next to the production code, e.g. pkgs/tasks/handler/handler_cycles_test.go
//
// Regression test for: PATCH /tasks/{id}/cycles/{cycleId} panicked on cycleId=0.
// Original symptom (YYYY-MM-DD): nil cycle pointer dereferenced after lookup miss.
func TestRegression_PatchCycle_does_not_panic_on_missing_id(t *testing.T) {
    h, _ := newHandlerWithSQLite(t) // helper from internal/tasktestdb + handler test setup

    req := httptest.NewRequest(http.MethodPatch, "/tasks/1/cycles/9999", strings.NewReader(`{}`))
    req.Header.Set("Content-Type", "application/json")
    rec := httptest.NewRecorder()

    // Must NOT panic. Must return a clean 404.
    require.NotPanics(t, func() { h.ServeHTTP(rec, req) })
    require.Equal(t, http.StatusNotFound, rec.Code)
}
```

### Go: race-class regression

```go
// Regression test for: SSE hub subscriber map mutated without lock under concurrent disconnect.
// Original symptom: -race detected concurrent map write in subscribers.
func TestRegression_Hub_concurrent_subscribe_unsubscribe_is_race_free(t *testing.T) {
    hub := newHub() // production constructor

    var wg sync.WaitGroup
    for i := 0; i < 50; i++ {
        wg.Add(1)
        go func() {
            defer wg.Done()
            sub := hub.Subscribe()
            time.Sleep(time.Microsecond)
            hub.Unsubscribe(sub)
        }()
    }
    wg.Wait()
    // Must finish; -race must not fire. Run with: go test -race
    require.Equal(t, 0, hub.SubscriberCount())
}
```

### Web: throw-in-render regression

```ts
// File next to the component, e.g. web/src/tasks/components/TaskCard.test.tsx
//
// Regression for: TaskCard threw on `task.assignees === undefined` after API field rename.
// Original symptom: white screen on /tasks list when any task lacked an assignees field.
import { render, screen } from "@testing-library/react";
import { describe, it, expect } from "vitest";
import { TaskCard } from "./TaskCard";

describe("TaskCard regression", () => {
  it("does not throw when task.assignees is undefined", () => {
    const task = makeTask({ assignees: undefined });
    expect(() => render(<TaskCard task={task} />)).not.toThrow();
    expect(screen.getByText(task.title)).toBeInTheDocument();
  });
});
```

