## §2 — INVARIANT LOCK-INS (P1)

The test asserts the invariant directly, not just that the specific input works. Future code that violates the invariant via a different path will also fail this test.

### Go: dual-write atomicity

```go
// Regression for: store.UpsertCyclePhase wrote task_cycle_phases but failed to write
// task_events when the JSON marshal failed mid-tx, leaving an orphan phase.
// Asserts the invariant: every phase write produces exactly one task_events row in the same tx.
func TestInvariant_UpsertCyclePhase_dual_writes_atomically(t *testing.T) {
    db := tasktestdb.OpenSQLite(t)
    s := store.New(db)

    phase := domain.TaskCyclePhase{ /* ... */ }
    err := s.UpsertCyclePhase(ctx, phase)
    require.NoError(t, err)

    var phaseCount, eventCount int64
    db.Model(&domain.TaskCyclePhase{}).Where("cycle_id = ?", phase.CycleID).Count(&phaseCount)
    db.Model(&domain.TaskEvent{}).Where("payload LIKE ?", "%cycle_phase_changed%").Count(&eventCount)
    require.Equal(t, phaseCount, eventCount, "every phase write must co-write a task_event in the same tx")

    // Now provoke a failure mid-tx; assert NEITHER row appears.
    badPhase := domain.TaskCyclePhase{ /* contrived to fail validation in events writer */ }
    _ = s.UpsertCyclePhase(ctx, badPhase)
    db.Model(&domain.TaskCyclePhase{}).Where("cycle_id = ?", badPhase.CycleID).Count(&phaseCount)
    db.Model(&domain.TaskEvent{}).Where("payload LIKE ?", "%"+badPhase.IDForLog()+"%").Count(&eventCount)
    require.Equal(t, int64(0), phaseCount)
    require.Equal(t, int64(0), eventCount)
}
```

### Web: optimistic update rollback

```ts
// Regression for: useUpdateTask did not roll back optimistic title change on server 500.
// Asserts the invariant: query cache reflects server state after a mutation error.
it("rolls back optimistic title update when the server returns 500", async () => {
  server.use(
    http.patch("/tasks/:id", () => HttpResponse.json({ error: "boom" }, { status: 500 }))
  );
  const { result } = renderHook(() => useUpdateTask(), { wrapper });
  // Seed cache with a known task
  queryClient.setQueryData(["tasks", "1"], { id: "1", title: "original" });

  await act(() => result.current.mutateAsync({ id: "1", title: "changed" }));

  expect(queryClient.getQueryData(["tasks", "1"])).toEqual({ id: "1", title: "original" });
});
```

