## §3 — CONCURRENCY / LIFECYCLE LOCK-INS (P2)

### Go: goroutine cleanup on context cancel

```go
// Regression for: agentReady worker leaked goroutine after caller cancelled ctx.
func TestRegression_Worker_exits_on_context_cancel(t *testing.T) {
    before := runtime.NumGoroutine()
    ctx, cancel := context.WithCancel(context.Background())

    w := newWorker(/* ... */)
    go w.Run(ctx)

    time.Sleep(20 * time.Millisecond) // let it start
    cancel()
    require.Eventually(t, func() bool {
        return runtime.NumGoroutine() <= before+1 // +1 tolerance for test goroutine
    }, time.Second, 10*time.Millisecond)
}
```

### Web: useEffect aborts in-flight fetch on unmount

```ts
// Regression for: useTask hook called setState after unmount when fetch landed late.
it("aborts the fetch when the consumer unmounts before the response", async () => {
  let aborted = false;
  server.use(
    http.get("/tasks/:id", async ({ request }) => {
      request.signal.addEventListener("abort", () => { aborted = true; });
      await new Promise((r) => setTimeout(r, 50));
      return HttpResponse.json({ id: "1" });
    })
  );
  const { unmount } = renderHook(() => useTask("1"), { wrapper });
  unmount();
  await new Promise((r) => setTimeout(r, 100));
  expect(aborted).toBe(true);
});
```

