## §6 — CONTRACT-DRIFT LOCK-INS (P5)

The test pins the wire format. If a future change breaks the contract, this test fires before clients break.

### Go: handler response shape

```go
// Regression for: PATCH /tasks/{id}/cycles/{cycleId}/phases/{seq} renamed
// "phaseStatus" → "status" in code without updating the doc, breaking the web client.
// Test pins the documented shape per docs/API-HTTP.md.
func TestContract_PatchPhase_response_shape(t *testing.T) {
    h, _ := newHandlerWithSQLiteAndSeededCycle(t)
    req := httptest.NewRequest(http.MethodPatch, "/tasks/1/cycles/1/phases/1",
        strings.NewReader(`{"status":"running"}`))
    req.Header.Set("Content-Type", "application/json")
    rec := httptest.NewRecorder()
    h.ServeHTTP(rec, req)
    require.Equal(t, http.StatusOK, rec.Code)

    var got map[string]any
    require.NoError(t, json.Unmarshal(rec.Body.Bytes(), &got))
    // Pin the documented field names — fail loudly if anything is renamed/removed.
    for _, field := range []string{"cycleId", "phaseSeq", "phase", "status", "startedAt"} {
        _, ok := got[field]
        require.True(t, ok, "response missing documented field %q", field)
    }
}
```

### Web: parser rejects unexpected shape

```ts
// Regression for: parseTaskApi.cycle silently coerced status="exploded" (not in enum)
// to "unknown", masking server-side bugs.
import { parseCycle } from "@/api/parseTaskApi";

it("rejects a cycle with an out-of-enum status", () => {
  const bad = { id: "1", status: "exploded", phases: [] };
  expect(() => parseCycle(bad)).toThrow(/status/i);
});

it("accepts every documented status", () => {
  for (const status of ["pending", "running", "succeeded", "failed", "cancelled"]) {
    expect(() => parseCycle({ id: "1", status, phases: [] })).not.toThrow();
  }
});
```

### Cross: SSE event name pinning

```go
// Regression for: SSE event renamed in handler from "task_changed" to "taskChanged"
// without updating the web subscriber, silently breaking real-time updates.
func TestContract_SSE_event_names_match_documented(t *testing.T) {
    documented := []string{"task_changed", "task_cycle_changed", "phase_changed"}
    // Read the constants/strings the handler uses
    emittedNames := collectEmittedEventNames(t) // helper that scans the handler package
    for _, name := range documented {
        require.Contains(t, emittedNames, name, "documented SSE event %q not emitted by handler", name)
    }
}
```

